        "richtext_BGg4YE": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h5><em><strong>Duties</strong></em></h5><ul><li><em>Care for animals (horses, cows, goats, and chickens) by feeding, watering, and monitoring their health.</em></li><li><em>Operate and maintain farm equipment such as tractors, forklifts, and other heavy machinery.</em></li><li><em>Assist with equipment repair as needed.</em></li><li><em>Utilize power tools for various farm projects.</em></li><li><em>Implement animal husbandry practices to ensure the well-being of all animals on the farm.</em></li><li><em>Perform heavy lifting tasks as required for moving supplies and equipment.</em></li></ul><h5><em><strong>Experience</strong></em></h5><p><em>Previous experience in farming or agricultural work is preferred, but not mandatory</em></p><ul><li><em>Familiarity with equine / bovine / avian / caprine care</em></li><li><em>Experience in operating heavy equipment safely and efficiently</em></li><li><em>Skills in equipment repair </em></li><li><em>A strong understanding of animal husbandry practices</em></li><li><em>Ability to work collaboratively with others while also being self-motivated</em></li></ul><p><em>Join our team today to contribute to sustainable farming practices while gaining valuable experience in the agricultural industry!</em></p><ul><li><em><strong>Job Type:</strong></em><em> Part-time (Possibility for Full-Time)</em></li><li><em><strong>Pay: TBD after initial call. </strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Benefits: </strong></em><em>Access to wellness / recovery amenities (saunas, cold plunge, gym, pool, hyperbaric chamber, various farm activities, exclusive networking opportunities, etc.)</em></li><li><em><strong>Schedule: </strong></em><em>2-3 days a week </em></li></ul><h5><em><strong>Work Location: </strong></em></h5><p><em><strong>Sweet Honey Farm </strong></em></p><p><em><strong>395 Tennent Road</strong></em></p><p><em><strong>Morganville, NJ 07751</strong></em></p>",
